The paper describes a reinforcement learning algorithm for learning in domains with continuous state spaces and stochastic, switching dynamics, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on a specific algorithm for learning in these domains. The second most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), as the paper uses a robotic car driving over varying terrain as an example to demonstrate the effectiveness of the algorithm. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with learning in complex, real-world domains. The fourth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper deals with stochastic, switching dynamics. The fifth likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), as the paper deals with learning in environments with multiple agents.
